entries.femaleVariant: How're things lookin', Miss V?
I got the Konpeki recording.
I met with Evelyn Parker.
Let's just say it was an interesting meet.
We'll talk about the rest at The Afterlife. See you there.
You run into any problems?
Evelyn surprised me. A few times.
She's sleeping with Yorinobu.
Evelyn threw a few surprises my way.
No shock to me.
Girl's got her secrets. Just like anybody who means a damn thing in this town.
Now, if her info was trash, that's when I'd start to worry…
She's slottin' Yorinobu Arasaka. Who also happens to be the guy we're gonna scrape the chip from.
Well, well, Yorinobu and Evelyn Parker... Goin' all nasty on each other. Seems Arasaka's prodigal son is hungry for attention again. Wonder whose toes he'll step on this time.
Should it?
This doesn't concern you at all?
We ain't here to sniff out all of Night City's dirtiest secrets. Let the media do that.
We got a job to do. So how 'bout we focus on that.
Great, be there in no time.
See ya, Miss V.
Turns out Evelyn's recording from Konpeki was worth our time.
Beautiful. T-Bug already called, said she's workin' her magic.
Got the bot.
Did it without Militech holdin' my hand. Didn't wanna risk it.
I met Stout.
Poor Meredith. No doubt in my mind she'll be left pickin' up the tab after your bad date.
Met with Stout. Managed to strike a deal.
You got some balls, Miss V.
entries.maleVariant: You got some balls, Mr. V.

entries.femaleVariant: She just forgot to mention the chip was packin' a virus.
One thing Stout forgot to mention. Chip was carryin' a virus.
I warned Royce. We made a deal.
Virus attacked their systems, scorched a handful of Maelstromers. I took care of the rest.
No. Paid the gang out of my own pocket.
Only way I know that always works. Brute force.
Sure. 'Course there was trouble. Royce couldn't've given two shits that you and Brick had shaken on it.
How'd you get him on board? You use the corpo woman?
So you paid for the Flathead with corp cash.
I got the Flathead.
On second thought, never mind.
Know what? Not important.
Everything's ready to roll. What now?
We're all set, ready to go. What now?
What about the meet with Evelyn Parker?
Still on the to-do list.
And the Flathead?
Nothin' yet. On it now.
Mhm.
T-Bug says no chance at the chip without that bot. To work, then, Miss V.
entries.maleVariant: T-Bug says no chance at the chip without that bot. To work, then, Mr. V.

entries.femaleVariant: Gave me the chip with the scratch for Maelstrom.
Well, well.
And?
Didn't exactly hit it off.
No. Decided I could use the eddies myself.
Oldest corpo trick in the book. I assume Royce was less than understanding?
Mhm. That meet's the only thing that'll get you a chance at grabbin' that chip.
And how'd it go? Run into any trouble? And what about the Militech angle?
So Militech financed our Flathead?
And I'll be sure to scan the Militech scratch before I try and use it.
Paid out of my own pocket.
That bot ain't no bargain basement tech.
That it is not.
And I just grabbed the bot.
Jus' like that…?
Not just. Had to use violence.
So how'd you get that cat Royce to hand over the Flathead?
Now we do the job I hired you to do – grabbing that biochip.
Parker'll be waiting for you at Lizzie's Bar. Good luck.
